<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="74" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Lithuania/23</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Lithuanian Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bizauskas</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-05-01"><hi rend="italic">May 1,
                                1924</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I have
                            been telegraphically instructed by my Government to communicate to you
                            that I am authorized by my Government to enter into negotiations with
                            the <pb facs="0250" n="136" xml:id="pg_136"/> Government of the United
                            States with regard to the settlement of the indebtedness of Lithuania to
                            the United States.</p>
                        <p>I should be very grateful if you will cause this to be communicated to
                            the World War Foreign Debt Commission.</p>
                        <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">K. Bizauskas</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>